(
<figureCitation box="[159,273,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 1–10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[286,357,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,529,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[162,1426,525,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 21 and 22, Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male. 23 and 24, T. vanessae sp. nov., holotype male. 25 and 26, T. clarkei Kramer, 1962, holotype male (USNM). 27 and 28, T. grandis Chiamolera &amp; Cavichioli, 2003, holotype male (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">21–22</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="419" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,510,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,510,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Crown (
<figureCitation box="[376,459,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,529,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[162,1426,525,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 21 and 22, Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male. 23 and 24, T. vanessae sp. nov., holotype male. 25 and 26, T. clarkei Kramer, 1962, holotype male (USNM). 27 and 28, T. grandis Chiamolera &amp; Cavichioli, 2003, holotype male (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) with rounded anterior margin. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[932,1000,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) with inner dorsal processes ventrally curved in apical third, not exceeding apex of pygofer. Subgenital plates, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1209,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) with dorsal margin expanded in median third; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[639,707,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), with lateral margins converging towards the apex, narrowed in apical third. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[418,519,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 8–9</figureCitation>
) with shaft asymmetrical and strongly flattened dorsoventrally, gonoduct distinct throughout length of shaft, apex slightly expanded. Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[859,975,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 3, 10</figureCitation>
) with short processes, with apices divergent and acute, outer margin with small denticles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="419" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,510,1689]" box="[199,828,726,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,453,726,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[525,627,726,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">holotype</typeStatus>
: total length 7.25.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,510,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,762,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body yellow (
<figureCitation box="[506,639,762,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,529,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[162,1426,525,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 21 and 22, Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male. 23 and 24, T. vanessae sp. nov., holotype male. 25 and 26, T. clarkei Kramer, 1962, holotype male (USNM). 27 and 28, T. grandis Chiamolera &amp; Cavichioli, 2003, holotype male (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 21–22</figureCitation>
). Crown yellow, without orange stripes. Face (
<figureCitation box="[1173,1239,762,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) without distinct marks. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[358,439,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,529,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[162,1426,525,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 21 and 22, Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male. 23 and 24, T. vanessae sp. nov., holotype male. 25 and 26, T. clarkei Kramer, 1962, holotype male (USNM). 27 and 28, T. grandis Chiamolera &amp; Cavichioli, 2003, holotype male (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) with two dark maculae adjacent to posterior margin. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1227,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) yellow semi-hyaline; anal margin and apical portion smoky. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[713,795,834,860]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,529,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[162,1426,525,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 21 and 22, Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male. 23 and 24, T. vanessae sp. nov., holotype male. 25 and 26, T. clarkei Kramer, 1962, holotype male (USNM). 27 and 28, T. grandis Chiamolera &amp; Cavichioli, 2003, holotype male (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,510,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,870,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">External morphology.</emphasis>
Crown (
<figureCitation box="[560,642,870,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,529,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[162,1426,525,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 21 and 22, Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male. 23 and 24, T. vanessae sp. nov., holotype male. 25 and 26, T. clarkei Kramer, 1962, holotype male (USNM). 27 and 28, T. grandis Chiamolera &amp; Cavichioli, 2003, holotype male (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) subquadrangular, with rounded anterior margin; coronal maculae distinct near posterior margin. Other characteristics as in description of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,510,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,401,942,968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[700,771,942,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), subtriangular, high at base and progressively narrowing towards apex, approximately twice as long as high; macrosetae present on apical third; ventral tooth on basal third, apex rounded; inner dorsal processes ventrally curved in apical third, not exceeding apex of pygofer, ventral margin with small irregular and rounded apical teeth. Subgenital plates, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1100,1050,1076]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) with dorsal margin expanded in median third forming a rounded lobe; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[813,882,1086,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), with lateral margins converging towards apex, narrowed in apical third; outer margin with microsetae in apical third. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1139,1122,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) approximately two-thirds of length of style. Style (
<figureCitation box="[425,525,1158,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 6–7</figureCitation>
) with base of apodeme bilobed, both lobes rounded and approximately same size; apophysis moderately curved dorsally; apical hook moderately developed. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1230,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 8–9</figureCitation>
) with shaft asymmetrical and strongly flattened dorsoventrally, slightly twisted; apex slightly expanded, with two small preapical lateral lobes; gonoduct distinct throughout length of the shaft. Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1120,1266,1292]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 3, 10</figureCitation>
) with short processes, with apices divergent and acute, outer margin with small denticles.
</paragraph>
