</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="419" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,510,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1518,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gonçalves &amp; Barbosa, 2021" authorityName="Gonçalves &amp; Barbosa" authorityYear="2021" box="[321,579,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tichocoelidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marceloi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[321,579,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Tichocoelidia marceloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[584,673,1518,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[584,673,1518,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1962" box="[797,901,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tichocoelidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clarkei">
<emphasis box="[797,901,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">T. clarkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the color pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1130,1344,1518,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,529,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[162,1426,525,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 21 and 22, Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male. 23 and 24, T. vanessae sp. nov., holotype male. 25 and 26, T. clarkei Kramer, 1962, holotype male (USNM). 27 and 28, T. grandis Chiamolera &amp; Cavichioli, 2003, holotype male (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 21–22, 25–26</figureCitation>
), shapes of aedeagus and processes of anal tube. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonçalves &amp; Barbosa, 2021" authorityName="Gonçalves &amp; Barbosa" authorityYear="2021" box="[707,834,1554,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tichocoelidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marceloi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[707,723,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[735,834,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">marceloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[840,928,1554,1580]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[840,928,1554,1580]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1962" box="[1073,1180,1554,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tichocoelidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clarkei">
<emphasis box="[1073,1089,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1102,1180,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">clarkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the pygofer. In the new species the ventral tooth arises on the basal third of the ventral margin and the inner processes are thin and curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[445,512,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1962" box="[631,738,1626,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tichocoelidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clarkei">
<emphasis box="[631,647,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[660,738,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">clarkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the ventral tooth is on the middle third and the inner processes are robust and strongly curved internally with crossed apices (
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer, J. P." box="[845,999,1662,1688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="419" pagination="101 - 105" refId="ref4303" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1962) A synopsis of Biza and a new allied genus (Homoptera: Cicadellidae: Neocoelidiinae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 75, 101 - 105." type="journal article" year="1962">Kramer 1962</bibRefCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1010,1096,1662,1688]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,179,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,179,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Tichocoelidia marceloi sp. nov., holotype male: 1, head, frontal view; 2, forewing; 3, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 5, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 6, connective and styles, dorsal view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, aedeagus, caudal view; 10 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1108,1139,1662,1688]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[154,1418,181,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–20. Tichocoelidia vanessae sp. nov., holotype male: 11, head, frontal view; 12, forewing; 13, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 15, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 16, connective and style, dorsal view; 17, style, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, lateral view; 19, aedeagus, caudal view; 20 processes of anal tube, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5511552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5511552/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="419">12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
